Description: Oval handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay fine light pink-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Production date: 139 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 143.)
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 206, 34. Name Lapheides. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0168.14.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1006)
